Well, you can&#39;t run a flame problem without a transport model - it  
needs to know how to compute diffusion coefficients and thermal  
conductivity somehow.   Can&#39;t you do what you want by giving all  
species identical transport parameters?  If not, you would need to do  
some C++ programming: derive a new transport manager class from class  
Transport, and in that class implement calculation of diffusion  
coefficients however you like.


